  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hirunika's request",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Member of Parliament Mrs. Hirunika Premachandra said that the last day of the struggle to free the country from the Rajapaksas should be on the 9th, and for that all parties should unite.",
        "While attending a press conference held at the office of the opposition leader in Colombo today (07), she stated that the ousting of President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa cannot be done by individual parties.",
        "\"This fight is the last fight, as I always say. It will be the last day to rid the country of the Rajapaksas. On that day, everyone should take to the streets regardless of party color. My personal opinion is that in order to protect the common people of the country, Sajaba, JVP, T All the NA and vanguards should join hands and stand together in front of the people as a great human wall, then the politicians in front will be the first to eat tear gas and water attacks.",
        "This is not something that a single party can do alone. Sahaba cannot oust the president alone. The JVP alone cannot oust the President. The defenders cannot do it alone. University student unions cannot do it alone. It can be done if all these people join together. So if the 9th is the last day, you have to prepare this week. Yesterday we went to the President's house. Today I think the monks came down. Tomorrow I think the university youths will be out. So the last day of all this is that he will go home on the 9th.",
        "No one needs to join here or become a leader of the struggle. Credit for this struggle should not go to anyone. People should take the credit for the struggle. Party politics are irrelevant at this time. Find out who our common enemy is. From the man who can to the man who can't, he roams the streets.\""
      ],
